The author is writing a nonfiction book about a particularly complex and challenging topic. In the following passage, the author describes the research process for the book.  

&quot;My initial research began with a deep dive into the existing body of academic work on this topic, and I found myself overwhelmed by the sheer number of studies, theories, and conflicting perspectives. The sheer volume of information was both daunting and exciting, for it revealed the breadth and complexity of the issue. I found myself needing to develop a framework to organize and understand the various approaches.  I tried to identify the key questions at the heart of the debate and to analyze how different scholars had addressed these questions. The process was a struggle at times, but it was ultimately rewarding.&quot;

What is the main idea of the passage?
